                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
            <p>
                <strong >Step 2</strong>
                Add the results of each multiplication together.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong >Step 3</strong>
                Divide the total by 11 and establish the remainder.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong >Step 4</strong>
                Subtract the remainder from 11 to give the check digit.
            </p>
            <p>
                If the result is 11 then a check digit of 0 is used. If the result is 10 then the number is invalid and not used.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong >Step 5</strong>
                Check the remainder matches the check digit. If it does not, the number  is invalid.
            </p>
